<h2 id="pivot">Pivot Table</h2>
<p>
    In database and statistics, reports are what you use to <strong> summarize</strong> and <strong> present</strong> data in the tables. A report usually answers a specific question, such as "How many under 5 children cured during this year?" or "Which provinces have the highest death rate?‚Äù. Each report can be formatted to present the information in the most readable way possible.
A report can be run at any time, and will always reflect the current data in the database. </p>
<p>
The nutrition reports are supposed to be viewed using <strong> Excel pivot table</strong> it is because of the flexibility of the program and convenience of users in working with Excel.
</p>
<p>
A pivot table report is an interactive table that quickly combines and compares large amounts of data. You can rotate its rows and columns to see different summaries of the source data, and you can display the details for areas of interest. In order to facilitate customized data analysis, the nutrition database has feature that the pivot table will be created automatically in Excel. This allows looking and examining data closely and doing different analysis from different angles. 
</p>
<p>
The data tabulation, frequency and percentage tables will be prepared automatically using the database in excel pivot table with just a single click. You can have full access to the data where you can simply copy and paste them with a little formatting that may be required. In addition, you can create your own simple and complex charts and graphs by arranging or organizing the data. 
</p>
