<h2 id="quality">Care for Quality of Data</h2>
<p>
    It is important to check the data that is being entered into database is accurate and reliable. Having no data is better than inaccurate data. Erroneous data may lead to wrong decisions. For example, an inaccurate record of patient‚Äôs reaction to penicillin may lead to a doctor to harm the patient while believing that she/he is helping him.
</p>
<p>
    Data accuracy or quality of data is not responsibility of one or two persons. It is everyone‚Äôs job. The typist, tally person, head of the project. But the accuracy of NUTRITION data is mostly dependent of tally person or the base where data is gathered namely the health facility is the base of accurate and inaccurate data. 
</p>
<p>
    The other person who is responsible for data quality is the person who enters data into database. He/she shall not only care about data entry while typing into database but he should make sure the data that enters into database is fine and make correction if there is any problem with the source data in the hard copy or tally. He should also make this ethic for him to double check data after every data entry of a report and regularly check quality of data using pivot table and provide feedback in order to minimize errors or mistakes in the data.
</p>
<p>
    In this paper we focus on the accuracy check of the data entered in the database. Database is not that wise to check if 4 odema for <6 children was recorded as 4 6-24 months. But it will check that duplicate record is not entered, alarm when total number of male and female is not matching with total number of new admission in MAM and do some other validation check.
</p>
<p>
    You may do the following checking and precautions during data entry or after data entry to monitor the quality of data entered into database:
</p>

<ul>
 <li>Before you enter data into database, check that the data you have collected is correct and complete</li>
 <li>Try to fill all of the blank fields</li>
 <li>While typing be very careful not to type 222 instead of 2</li>
 <li>Give full attention when typing and make sure you type on the right place and is not entered in the wrong place</li>
 <li>Have glance on data that is very big or seems unusual and correct if any</li>
 <li>Big number of refer in, deaths, defaulters and other requires full attention</li>
 <li>Make sure the total number of exits is not bigger than total admission</li>
 <li>Make sure total at the end is not negative number</li>
 <li>Make full attention to red colors in the data entry screens</li>
 <li>Make sure data is complete</li>
</ul>

<p>
    When analyzing data you may consider the following items:</p>
    <li>Look for large gaps in the data</li>
    <li>Look for unusual month to month variations</li>
    <li>Check for duplication in reporting or repetitive</li>
    <li>Check for inconsistencies ‚Äì unlikely values</li>
    <li>Look for data present where there should not be</li>
    <li>There might be typing errors if there is a very large data</li>
    <li>Check that data is not entered in wrong places</li>


